\b  
\pi1
\v 60 \w Altogether|strong="H3605"\w*, \w there|strong="H3605"\w* \w were|strong="H1121"\w* 392 \w temple|strong="H5411"\w* workers \w and|strong="H3967"\w* \w descendants|strong="H1121"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w Solomon|strong="H8010"\w*’s \w servants|strong="H5650"\w* \w who|strong="H3605"\w* returned.   
\b  
\pi1
\v 61-62 Another group of 642 people from the clans of Delaiah, Tobiah, and Nekoda also returned. They came from the towns of Tel-Melah, Tel-Harsha, Kerub, Addan (\add which is also known as Addon\add*), and Immer \add in Babylonia\add*. But they could not prove that they were descendants of Israelis.   
\b  
\pi1
\v 63 \w Priests|strong="H3548"\w* \w from|strong="H4480"\w* \w the|strong="H5921"\w* clans \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w Hobaiah|strong="H2252"\w*, \w Hakkoz|strong="H6976"\w*, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w Barzillai|strong="H1271"\w* \w also|strong="H8034"\w* returned. \w Barzillai|strong="H1271"\w* \w had|strong="H3548"\w* \w married|strong="H3947"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w woman|strong="H1323"\w* \w who|strong="H3548"\w* \w is|strong="H8034"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w descendant|strong="H1121"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \add a man named\add* \w Barzillai|strong="H1271"\w* \w from|strong="H4480"\w* \add the\add* Gilead \add region\add*, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* \w he|strong="H4480"\w* \w had|strong="H3548"\w* \w taken|strong="H3947"\w* \w his|strong="H7121"\w* wife’s family \w name|strong="H8034"\w*.  
\v 64 \w They|strong="H3808"\w* \w searched|strong="H1245"\w* \w in|strong="H4672"\w* \w the|strong="H4480"\w* records \w that|strong="H4480"\w* contained \w the|strong="H4480"\w* names \w of|strong="H4480"\w* \w people|strong="H3808"\w*’s ancestors, \w but|strong="H3808"\w* \w they|strong="H3808"\w* could \w not|strong="H3808"\w* \w find|strong="H4672"\w* \w the|strong="H4480"\w* names \w of|strong="H4480"\w* \w those|strong="H4480"\w* clans, \w so|strong="H4480"\w* \w they|strong="H3808"\w* \w were|strong="H4672"\w* \w not|strong="H3808"\w* allowed \w to|strong="H1245"\w* \w have|strong="H4672"\w* \w the|strong="H4480"\w* rights \w and|strong="H4480"\w* duties \w that|strong="H4480"\w* \w priests|strong="H3808"\w* \w have|strong="H4672"\w* right \w away|strong="H4480"\w*.  
\v 65 \w The|strong="H5704"\w* \w governor|strong="H8660"\w* told \w them|strong="H5975"\w* \w that|strong="H3548"\w* \w before|strong="H5704"\w* \w they|strong="H3808"\w* could eat \w the|strong="H5704"\w* food offered \w as|strong="H5704"\w* \w sacrifices|strong="H6944"\w*, \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w priest|strong="H3548"\w* \w should|strong="H3548"\w* use \w the|strong="H5704"\w* marked stones \add to find out what God said about their being priests\add*.   
\b  
\pi1
\v 66 \w Altogether|strong="H3605"\w*, \w there|strong="H3605"\w* \w were|strong="H7969"\w* 42,360 people \w who|strong="H3605"\w* returned \w to|strong="H3605"\w* Judea.  
\v 67 There \w were|strong="H5650"\w* also 7,337 \w of|strong="H5650"\w* their \w servants|strong="H5650"\w*, \w and|strong="H3967"\w* 245 \w singers|strong="H7891"\w*, which included \w men|strong="H5650"\w* \w and|strong="H3967"\w* \w women|strong="H7891"\w*.  
\v 68 \w The|strong="H3967"\w* Israelis \w also|strong="H1581"\w* brought back \add from Babylonia\add* 736 horses, 245 mules,  
\v 69 435 camels, \w and|strong="H3967"\w* 6,720 donkeys.   
\b  
\pi1
\v 70 Some \w of|strong="H7218"\w* \w the|strong="H5414"\w* \w leaders|strong="H7218"\w* \w of|strong="H7218"\w* \w the|strong="H5414"\w* clans \w gave|strong="H5414"\w* gifts \w for|strong="H3701"\w* \w the|strong="H5414"\w* \w work|strong="H4399"\w* \add of rebuilding the temple\add*. \w I|strong="H5414"\w*, being \w the|strong="H5414"\w* governor, \w gave|strong="H5414"\w* ◄17 pounds/8.6 kg.► \w of|strong="H7218"\w* \w gold|strong="H2091"\w*, 50 bowls \add to be used in the temple\add*, \w and|strong="H3967"\w* 530 robes \w for|strong="H3701"\w* \w the|strong="H5414"\w* priests.  
\v 71 \w Some|strong="H5971"\w* \w of|strong="H7611"\w* \w the|strong="H5414"\w* leaders \w of|strong="H7611"\w* \w the|strong="H5414"\w* clans \w gave|strong="H5414"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* total \w of|strong="H7611"\w* ◄337 pounds/153 kg.► \w of|strong="H7611"\w* \w gold|strong="H2091"\w*, \w and|strong="H3701"\w* ◄3,215 pounds/1,460 kg.► \w of|strong="H7611"\w* \w silver|strong="H3701"\w*.  
\v 72 \w The|strong="H3605"\w* rest \w of|strong="H1121"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w people|strong="H5971"\w* gave \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w total|strong="H3605"\w* \w of|strong="H1121"\w* ◄337 pounds/153 kg.► \w of|strong="H1121"\w* gold, ◄2,923 pounds/1,330 kg.► \w of|strong="H1121"\w* silver, \w and|strong="H1121"\w* 67 robes \w for|strong="H3427"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w priests|strong="H3548"\w*.   
\pi1
\v 73 So the priests, the \add other\add* descendants of Levi \add who helped the priests\add*, the temple guards, the musicians, the temple workers, and many ordinary people, who were all Israelis, started to live in the towns and cities of Judea \add where their ancestors had lived\add*.   
\c 8  
\s1 Ezra read from the laws of Moses  
\p
\v 1-2 Ezra, who taught people the laws of Moses, \add had a scroll on which\add* the laws of Moses were written. Those were the laws that \w Yahweh|strong="H3068"\w* had commanded the Israeli people \add to obey\add*. On October 8 of that year, all the people gathered together in the plaza/square that was close to the Water Gate. Men and women and \add children\add* who \add were old enough to\add* understand gathered together. Someone told Ezra to bring out that scroll.  
\v 3 \w So|strong="H4480"\w* \w he|strong="H3117"\w* brought \w it|strong="H7121"\w* \w out|strong="H4480"\w* \w and|strong="H3117"\w* \w read|strong="H7121"\w* \w it|strong="H7121"\w* \w to|strong="H5704"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w people|strong="H5971"\w*. \w He|strong="H3117"\w* started \w reading|strong="H7121"\w* \w it|strong="H7121"\w* early \w in|strong="H3117"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* morning \w and|strong="H3117"\w* continued \w reading|strong="H7121"\w* \w it|strong="H7121"\w* \w until|strong="H5704"\w* noontime. \w All|strong="H3605"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w people|strong="H5971"\w* listened \w carefully|strong="H3605"\w* \w to|strong="H5704"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w laws|strong="H8451"\w* \w that|strong="H5971"\w* \w were|strong="H5971"\w* written \w on|strong="H3117"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* \w scroll|strong="H5612"\w*.   
\p
