\v 38 “However, \w we|strong="H3068"\w* \add Israeli\add* people now are making an agreement/promise \add to obey you\add*, and \w we|strong="H3068"\w* are writing this agreement/promise \add on a scroll\add*. We will write on it the names of our leaders and the names of the Levites and the names of the priests, and then \w we|strong="H3068"\w* will seal it.”   
\c 10  
\s1 Those who signed the agreement  
\p
\v 1 ◄\w This|strong="H2063"\w* \w is|strong="H3605"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* list/\w These|strong="H2063"\w* \w are|strong="H3548"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* names► \w of|strong="H8269"\w* \w those|strong="H3605"\w* \w who|strong="H3605"\w* \w signed|strong="H3789"\w* \w the|strong="H3605"\w* agreement:  
\b  
\li1 I, Nehemiah, the governor; and also Zedekiah.   
\b  
\m
\v 2 \w The|strong="H5921"\w* priests \w who|strong="H1121"\w* signed \w it|strong="H5921"\w* \w were|strong="H1121"\w*:  
\li1 Seraiah, Azariah, Jeremiah,   
\li1
\v 3 Pashhur, Amariah, Malkijah,   
\li1
\v 4 Hattush, Shebaniah, Malluch,   
\li1
\v 5 Harim, Meremoth, Obadiah,   
\li1
\v 6 Daniel, Ginnethon, Baruch,   
\li1
\v 7 Meshullam, Abijah, Mijamin,   
\li1
\v 8 Maaziah, Bilgai, and Shemaiah.   
\b  
\m
\v 9 \w The|strong="H3548"\w* \add other\add* descendants \w of|strong="H3548"\w* Levi \w who|strong="H3548"\w* signed it were:  
\li1 Jeshua the son of Azaniah, Binnui from the clan of Henadad, Kadmiel,   
\li1
\v 10 Shebaniah, Hodiah, Kelita, Pelaiah, Hanan,   
\li1
\v 11 Mica, Rehob, Hashabiah,   
\li1
\v 12 Zaccur, Sherebiah, Shebaniah,   
\li1
\v 13 Hodiah, Bani, and Beninu.   
\b  
\m
\v 14 \w The|strong="H1137"\w* Israeli leaders who signed it were:  
\li1 Parosh, Pahath-Moab, Elam, Zattu, Bani,   
\li1
\v 15 Bunni, Azgad, Bebai,   
\li1
\v 16 Adonijah, Bigvai, Adin,   
\li1
\v 17 Ater, Hezekiah, Azzur,   
\li1
\v 18 Hodiah, Hashum, Bezai,   
\li1
